What is linux? a kernel, os, and huge open-source success
Why is the linux penguin so funny-looking? it is fat
What is the penguin's name? Tux
What is a distro? short for Linux distribution
What is a distro? an operating system which uses the Linux kernel, but does its own thing at the application level
What is GNU? an acronym for GNU's not Unix
What is GNU? a way for people to use a product like Unix for free and for programmers anywhere and everywhere to contribute to this and other related open-source projects
Why should I care what the Free Software Foundation thinks? they do in fact have good ideas about high-quality coding and a better working environment through free and open source software
